						<summary>

						<p>This is also in modern characters and is indifferently worded. It is dated in Hēviḷambi, Vaigāśi, 15, Thursday, and records the formation of a flower garden on 200 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of land at Kannār to the south-east of Vairavan-kēṇi by one Ellappa Reḍḍi (?) with the help of Saiyid Vibaramu (Ibrahim) Sāyabu and Venkaṭādri-Mudaliār the <hi rend="italic">Pārapatyam</hi> of Vallappakkam and also the residents of the village.</p>						

						</summary>
